description:
Signed variant of the Ude (C# port of Mozilla Universal Charset Detector) - http://code.google.com/p/ude/
    
    I tried to contact with owner of the https://www.nuget.org/packages/UDE.CSharp/ for simple signing lib... but no results
    
    In general, this release of the signed library of the main project - http://code.google.com/p/ude/
    / Licenses, features, version number, bugs etc. :) all the same as in primary...
        
    Why not the https://www.nuget.org/packages/UDE.CSharp/ ?
    
    Library above not signed, therefore we can't sign any other lib, because the ~signed assemblies can't use the unsigned - for more details, see about error "Referenced assembly does not have a strong name"
    
    Well, if you see a similar problems with UDE.CSharp, you can try this... should all work
    
    ---
    assembled from: https://bitbucket.org/3F/ude.signed
